itnesses to give evidence effectively. This book contains the Act’s main provisions together with commentary to help you to understand it fully. Informed by the authors’ experience of vulnerable witnesses in practice, the book provides an essential reference for lawyers, law students, those who lead or hear witness in court and other professionals dealing with young people and adults who may be vulnerable as potential witnesses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCriminal justice, Administration ofzScotland. 0aExamination of witnesseszScotland. 4aLaw. 7aLAW / Practical Guides.2bisacsh1 aRoss, Margaret, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z97831107804680 cprintz978184586045540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748699537?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748699537423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748699537/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK